[22]Once the structure is completed, among the various currents were inserted wooden forms that competed to create a smooth surface on which was lying the coating consists of wooden slats glued to forty-five degrees on the structure and crossed at ninety degrees from one layer of lamellae to another.It is evident that a similar procedure was extremely slow and therefore does not allow for a high production rate, was also not executable by all companies in the aeronautic, in fact, in addition to the CRDA only the IMAM and, in the course of 1943, the Piaggio built aircraft.The CANT Z. 1007bis-series were produced with the tail vertical tail in two different versions (the two versions are not generally considered to be variations): War mondialeQuando Italy entered the war on 10 June 1940, the Regia Aeronautica had only two Flocks equipped with the "Alcione".
[23]One was the 16th, with 31 aircraft, provided, however, engines, Isotta Fraschini, and therefore declared "war".
